<BYLINE>By TERENCE HUNT</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP White House Correspondent</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Congressional leaders are pressing President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> for tough action against <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> but the <ORGANIZATION> White </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> is appealing for patience, saying it will be a long time before <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION> return to normal relations. White House press secretary <PERSON> Marlin </PERSON> <PERSON> Fitzwater </PERSON> said <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>, in a meeting with senators Friday, asked for `` their understanding that he was trying to do the best job possible to express the concerns of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> government, the outrage of <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> people in terms of what they had seen there, and at the same time, to preserve our relations as best we could.'' Sen. <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Biden </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Del </LOCATION>, said <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> `` asked for our patience and forbearance.'' Chinese authorities this week executed 27 people charged with taking part in pro-democracy demonstrations. On <LOCATION> Capitol </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hill </LOCATION>, calls continued for a stronger <ORGANIZATION> White </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> response. Sen. <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> C. </PERSON> <PERSON> Byrd </PERSON>, D-W. <LOCATION> Va. </LOCATION>, said: `` I believe the president must take tough action and block trade with and new investments in <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> right now He added that `` there are some values which take precedence over commerce.'' `` The stark barbarism of the communist regime is unforgivable to all civilized people,'' <PERSON> Byrd </PERSON> said. `` The dust has settled on the blood of peaceful demonstrators, and the regime wantonly spills fresh blood on top of old. It executes its young on the altar of old men's egos and fears. <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> can not possibly be in the posi