re delicate, appropriate, judgmental handling of the situation.'' Sen. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Kerry </PERSON>, D-Mass., said the acts of the <LOCATION> Chinese </LOCATION> government against its own citizens `` must be met by an unrelenting and unmistakable willingness to change immediately and significantly the status quo of our relationship. `` The bullets aimed at pro-democracy students, workers and teachers are also aimed at us,'' <PERSON> Kerry </PERSON> said. `` Each shot that takes a life, when met by silence, indifference or sense of impotence, also takes with it a piece of who we are and what we are supposed to stand for.''
