<HEAD>Two Temblors Shake Wyoming Residents Out Of Bed</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: INSERTS 1 graf after 2nd graf with quote from woman in Jackson.
Picks up 3rd graf pvs, `The first...'.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JACKSON, Wyo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Two moderate earthquakes shook residents awake early today, but no damage or injuries were reported, a spokeswoman said. Two temblors, each measuring 4.1 on the <PERSON> Richter </PERSON> scale of ground motion, struck five miles north of the town of <LOCATION> Jackson </LOCATION>, said <PERSON> Pat </PERSON> <PERSON> Jorgenson </PERSON>, a spokeswoman for the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Geological Survey in <LOCATION> Golden </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Colo. </LOCATION> `` Well it really shook. I mean, you know, the windows rattled and you could just feel it,'' said <PERSON> Joanne </PERSON> <PERSON> Cross </PERSON>, who works at the Wort Hotel in <LOCATION> Jackson </LOCATION>. `` I thought, is somebody having a fight upstairs and breaking the furniture or are we having an earthquake? It was just a little hard to really tell.'' The first jolt hit at 3:25 a.m. MDT and the second temblor shook the area at 4:25 a.m. MDT, Ms. <PERSON> Jorgenson </PERSON> said. It was not immediately known whether the second shaker was an aftershock of the first quake, she said. A fault system has not yet been identified in the area of the temblors, although there have been earthquakes there in the past, she said. `` It has been some time since they have had any of this magnitude,'' Ms. <PERSON> Jorgenson </PERSON> said. The Richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an earthquake, as measured by the ground motion recorded on a seismograph. Every increase of one number means a tenfold increase in magnitude, or the height of quake-generated shock waves recorded on a seismograph. An earthquake of 3.5 on the <PERSON> Richter </PERSON> scale can cause slight damage in the local area, 4 moderate damage, 5 considerable damage, 6 severe damage.
