ION> N.Y. </LOCATION>, who wanted to settle the rest of the estate. Ready said they had a choice between dividing everything and selling it item by item or having an auction. She hopes to buy her aunt's half of the house with her proceeds from the auction. <PERSON> Donahue </PERSON>, 71, said she regretted parting with family heirlooms, but felt she needed to because of financial reasons. But she was pleased to see some of the articles stay in the public domain. `` I would like to see the whole country get to know <PERSON> Josiah </PERSON> and what he did,'' she said.
